I have a repository with a sub-repository that is not listed at all in the "_Subrepositories_" section. The {{.hgsub}} file is like:

{{dir1/dir2/repo = HTTPS-TO-HG-REPOSITORY}}

In addition I have a couple of Mercurial projects where the "_Subrepositories_" section lists only the first and third entries. The failing configuration on both projects (file {{.hgsub}}) is:

{{dir1/dir1-1/repo = [git]HTTPS-TO-GIT-REPOSITORY}}
{{ dir2/dir2-1/repo = HTTPS-TO-HG-REPOSITORY}}
{{ dir2/dir2-2/repo = HTTPS-TO-HG-REPOSITORY}}

It will be very helpful if sorting/grouping/filtering is supported in file list views, especially in "staged files" view when there is a huge merge.

As with command line, I can quickly review a merge before commit with:

{{git status | grep "new file"  to see what's new/modified/deleted}}

{{git status | grep ".java$"    to see java relevant changes}}
